---
/**
 * @file AboutIntro.astro
 * @description Introduction section explaining collective mission, core principles, and disclaimer.
 */
---

<section
	class="bg-mapa-canvas-dark border-t border-mapa-contour/60 py-16 md:py-24 font-serif"
>
	<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
			<!-- LEFT COLUMN: What mapaPH is -->
			<div class="lg:col-span-5 flex flex-col justify-start">
				<div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
					<span
						class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-mapa-green"
					>
						About the Project
					</span>
				</div>

				<h2
					class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-mapa-ink leading-tight"
				>
					A collaborative ecosystem for Philippine web tools.
				</h2>

				<div
					class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 mt-6 space-y-4 leading-relaxed"
				>
					<p>
						mapaPH is a hub for tools built around maps of the
						Philippines. We build useful open-source utilities using
						the Philippine map as basis to work with locations,
						routes, transit, or anything else tied to a place.
					</p>
					<p>
						Every project is built openly on GitHub. Anyone can look
						at the code, contribute, or build their own tool on top
						of what's already here.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<!-- RIGHT COLUMN: Core principles (separated with a vertical line on desktop) -->
			<div class="lg:col-span-7 flex flex-col justify-center border-t border-mapa-contour/40 pt-12 mt-12 lg:border-t-0 lg:border-l lg:border-mapa-contour/60 lg:pt-0 lg:mt-0 lg:pl-16">
				<div class="space-y-8">
					<!-- First item aligns with the top of the left column content -->
					<div>
						<h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-mapa-ink">
							Map-First
						</h3>
						<p
							class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/80 mt-2 leading-relaxed"
						>
							We build around the Philippine map to show
							locations, transit, and data tied to a place.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/80 pt-6">
						<h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-mapa-ink">
							Lightweight
						</h3>
						<p
							class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/80 mt-2 leading-relaxed"
						>
							Fast, simple tools that work well alone or combined
							with the others.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-t border-mapa-contour/80 pt-6">
						<h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-bold text-mapa-ink">
							Community-driven
						</h3>
						<p
							class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/80 mt-2 leading-relaxed"
						>
							Anyone can shape what comes next. Contribute, share
							local knowledge, or build a new tool on top of
							what's already here.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- Bottom Disclaimer Note (rendered full-width outside the columns layout) -->
		<div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-mapa-contour/60">
			<p
				class="font-sans text-xs text-mapa-ink/60 leading-relaxed italic max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center"
			>
				Note: mapaPH is an independent, community-led open-source
				index. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or
				representative of the Philippine government or any of its
				municipal departments.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
